  "title": "Fertilizer use in semi-srid tropical India: The case of high-yielding varieties of sorghum and pearl millet",
  "abstract": "Sorghum and pearl millet are the two most important cereals grown on drylands in semi-arid tropical (SAT) areas of india. These have traditionally formed part of a highly unstable, low-cost, low-output farminq system and are evaluated in the market as relatively inferior foodgrains (Jodha 1973)...",
